
This week the Maricopa County Library Districtannounced their latest service, a virtual library offering librarycustomers 24/7 access to an online collection of hundreds of downloadabledigital Audiobooks and eBooks.  With the new service, customers can nowlogon, check out, and download a digital book anytime of day.  The digitalbooks can be enjoyed on customer's own computer or transferred to aportable device like a PDA, smart phone, or a portable audio device.Library customers can also burn Audiobooks to a standard CD, making it easyto enjoy them in the comfort of their air-conditioned living room, cars, oranywhere they like. The online library is available to all Maricopa CountyLibrary District customers by visiting http://mcld.maricopa.gov.

